1
00:00:29,930 --> 00:00:32,170
Well... I'm planning
to write a BL novel

2
00:00:32,400 --> 00:00:33,799
to pay off the debt.

3
00:00:33,800 --> 00:00:37,599
You think your BL novel
will save this house?

4
00:00:37,600 --> 00:00:38,320
Of course.

5
00:00:38,321 --> 00:00:39,920
Guy, how about we give this a try?

6
00:00:41,600 --> 00:00:43,040
You hit your head on something?

7
00:00:43,680 --> 00:00:44,680
No.

8
00:00:45,520 --> 00:00:46,520
I'm serious.

9
00:00:47,000 --> 00:00:48,000
Why?

10
00:00:52,640 --> 00:00:53,640
Well...

11
00:00:55,160 --> 00:00:56,160
Wanna try, I guess.

12
00:00:57,080 --> 00:00:59,760
How do you feel about me? Be honest.

13
00:01:01,360 --> 00:01:04,240
I can't say I like you yet.

14
00:01:05,080 --> 00:01:07,680
But I just wanna try. Is that okay?

15
00:01:13,440 --> 00:01:14,640
You're sure about this?

16
00:01:16,980 --> 00:01:18,400
Am I dreaming right now?

17
00:01:21,330 --> 00:01:22,330
Ow.

18
00:01:23,760 --> 00:01:25,240
Believe me now?

19
00:01:29,600 --> 00:01:30,760
Thanks, man.

20
00:01:37,090 --> 00:01:39,560
But... can I ask you something?

21
00:01:40,520 --> 00:01:41,520
Go ahead.

22
00:01:41,800 --> 00:01:43,360
Do not tell anyone about this.

23
00:01:44,440 --> 00:01:45,440
Sure.

24
00:01:49,920 --> 00:01:51,040
Thanks a lot, man.

25
00:02:11,850 --> 00:02:12,850
What is this?

26
00:02:19,840 --> 00:02:21,960
Phi Kenshin was running,
and then...

27
00:02:22,240 --> 00:02:25,279
Um, he fell into
a lava chocolate pit.

28
00:02:25,280 --> 00:02:27,120
And he was sinking.

29
00:02:28,680 --> 00:02:29,840
Sinking.

30
00:02:30,010 --> 00:02:31,359
Um... then...

31
00:02:31,360 --> 00:02:36,239
Then Phi Tonggao
turned into a merman,

32
00:02:36,240 --> 00:02:39,600
dove in, and pulled
Phi Kenshin out.

33
00:02:40,880 --> 00:02:41,880
Hey.

34
00:02:45,440 --> 00:02:49,960
And... the two of them locked eyes.

35
00:02:50,990 --> 00:02:51,990
Kissed.

36
00:02:53,290 --> 00:02:54,640
Kissed.

37
00:02:55,670 --> 00:02:58,480
They kissed and lived happily
ever after.

38
00:02:58,960 --> 00:02:59,960
What?

39
00:03:00,690 --> 00:03:01,919
That's how it ends?

40
00:03:01,920 --> 00:03:04,110
Yes, a happy ending.

41
00:03:05,050 --> 00:03:06,920
Can I read it, Director?

42
00:03:09,200 --> 00:03:10,600
Thank you.

43
00:03:11,130 --> 00:03:12,130
Come on.

44
00:03:18,400 --> 00:03:21,080
I think it's not that bad.

45
00:03:21,840 --> 00:03:25,560
Face it. It's no better than
what Grandpa writes himself.

46
00:03:25,880 --> 00:03:26,880
Hey, hey.

47
00:03:28,400 --> 00:03:32,280
I let you throw in your ideas.
You already say it's not good.

48
00:03:33,990 --> 00:03:37,070
I guess I'm giving up
on the BL novel.

49
00:03:39,130 --> 00:03:41,360
Let's try again.

50
00:03:41,390 --> 00:03:43,230
We'll start with...

51
00:03:43,450 --> 00:03:47,440
Phi Gasbell, a stone-faced
senior engineering student.

52
00:03:47,920 --> 00:03:51,320
Um... He liked playing with slime.

53
00:03:52,280 --> 00:03:55,760
One day, he went out
to buy a hair clip.

54
00:03:56,510 --> 00:03:58,340
But... um...

55
00:04:03,160 --> 00:04:07,280
But the shop was closed,
so he ended up at...

56
00:04:08,520 --> 00:04:09,520
a watermelon shop.

57
00:04:10,320 --> 00:04:11,640
And he ran into...

58
00:04:12,600 --> 00:04:14,640
Mara, a sweet-faced junior.

59
00:04:16,060 --> 00:04:18,840
Sweet-faced junior.

60
00:04:20,720 --> 00:04:23,000
Sweet-faced, um...

61
00:04:23,640 --> 00:04:25,240
And... they fell for each other.

62
00:04:35,640 --> 00:04:36,640
Grandpa.

63
00:04:37,280 --> 00:04:39,720
Come on, first scene, quick.

64
00:04:40,120 --> 00:04:42,200
- Hurry, hurry.
- What's going on?

65
00:04:42,910 --> 00:04:43,950
Come sit down.

66
00:04:46,030 --> 00:04:47,030
Quick.

67
00:04:50,300 --> 00:04:51,300
Come on.

68
00:04:52,090 --> 00:04:54,040
Grandpa, write fast before I forget.

69
00:04:55,120 --> 00:04:57,560
Quick. Starting with the confession.

70
00:04:58,120 --> 00:04:59,120
Hold on.

71
00:04:59,400 --> 00:05:00,400
Write it down. Fast.

72
00:05:01,250 --> 00:05:05,600
It's like heart pounding,
sweating, breathing all off.

73
00:05:05,880 --> 00:05:08,280
The sun's blazing
but it feels cold.

74
00:05:08,470 --> 00:05:10,840
- Oh, like getting ill.
- Yeah.

75
00:05:10,900 --> 00:05:12,160
- Follow along.
- Hmm?

76
00:05:12,230 --> 00:05:15,120
It's a major turning point
for a straight guy

77
00:05:16,680 --> 00:05:19,080
who's always brushed his teeth
with his right,

78
00:05:19,100 --> 00:05:19,820
Mm-hmm.

79
00:05:19,840 --> 00:05:21,479
Now switching to his left hand.

80
00:05:21,480 --> 00:05:23,830
- Yes, awkward, but gotta give in.
- Yeah.

81
00:05:23,850 --> 00:05:25,720
- No, scratch that, too thin.
- No?

82
00:05:25,740 --> 00:05:26,740
A bit slight.

83
00:05:26,920 --> 00:05:29,740
It's like... you've had espresso
every morning.

84
00:05:29,760 --> 00:05:30,510
Yeah.

85
00:05:30,540 --> 00:05:31,809
Now you switch to cold milk.

86
00:05:31,810 --> 00:05:33,910
- From coffee to sweet milk.
- Exactly.

87
00:05:33,950 --> 00:05:34,980
Yeah, that's odd.

88
00:05:35,000 --> 00:05:37,770
- No, no. It's more like...
- Hmm?

89
00:05:38,800 --> 00:05:40,960
You've liked women your whole life.

90
00:05:40,980 --> 00:05:42,779
But now you're switching to men.

91
00:05:42,780 --> 00:05:43,839
That one lands.

92
00:05:43,840 --> 00:05:44,959
- Yeah.
- Ah!

93
00:05:44,960 --> 00:05:46,000
You get it?

94
00:05:46,720 --> 00:05:48,120
Got it.

95
00:05:48,540 --> 00:05:51,520
Save, everything you
just spilled out...

96
00:05:52,480 --> 00:05:53,680
where did it come from?

97
00:05:55,000 --> 00:05:57,040
All those details you described...

98
00:05:57,540 --> 00:06:00,810
make me feel like you lived it.

99
00:06:02,320 --> 00:06:05,319
I'm trying things out with a guy.

100
00:06:05,320 --> 00:06:08,479
What? You're seeing a guy?

101
00:06:08,480 --> 00:06:10,120
Grandpa, keep it down.

102
00:06:10,960 --> 00:06:11,960
Shh.

103
00:06:12,800 --> 00:06:13,960
You said...

104
00:06:15,440 --> 00:06:17,640
You said you weren't into boys.

105
00:06:18,360 --> 00:06:21,600
Well... I want to help you
write the novel.

106
00:06:22,440 --> 00:06:25,239
Stop right there.
Don't go any further.

107
00:06:25,240 --> 00:06:27,680
You don't have to go that far.

108
00:06:27,920 --> 00:06:30,759
Not far at all. It's totally easy.

109
00:06:30,760 --> 00:06:34,990
Easy, huh?
No need to go to such lengths.

110
00:06:35,570 --> 00:06:38,600
I'm just giving it a try.
No harm done.

111
00:06:39,000 --> 00:06:40,400
- But...
- Grandpa.

112
00:06:41,040 --> 00:06:42,040
Trust me.

113
00:06:42,750 --> 00:06:45,840
If it doesn't work out,
I'll just stop.

114
00:06:46,320 --> 00:06:48,840
I'll find another way to help you.
Okay?

115
00:06:54,880 --> 00:06:56,000
You sure about this?

116
00:06:56,400 --> 00:06:57,400
Mm-hmm.

117
00:06:57,480 --> 00:06:59,280
Won't change your mind?

118
00:06:59,380 --> 00:07:01,640
I made up my mind. I'll do this.

119
00:07:04,720 --> 00:07:08,480
Oh, do not tell Mom and Dad.

120
00:07:08,720 --> 00:07:11,040
Keep this between us.

121
00:07:11,770 --> 00:07:12,770
Okay?

122
00:07:17,170 --> 00:07:18,280
Hmph. Grandpa.

123
00:07:46,720 --> 00:07:49,360
Hey... hey.

124
00:07:53,380 --> 00:07:57,139
Wah, wah...

125
00:07:57,140 --> 00:07:58,720
There. That's the sound.

126
00:08:00,110 --> 00:08:01,959
Were you imagining things?

127
00:08:01,960 --> 00:08:05,040
It's real. Goosebumps. See?

128
00:08:06,960 --> 00:08:08,080
Grandpa.

129
00:08:08,600 --> 00:08:10,160
Hmm? What is it?

130
00:08:10,680 --> 00:08:12,360
This house also has a child ghost?

131
00:08:13,640 --> 00:08:16,240
Jedi saw a girl ghost last night.

132
00:08:17,370 --> 00:08:18,480
You were dreaming.

133
00:08:20,440 --> 00:08:25,160
I've been here all my life.
Nobody's ever died here.

134
00:08:30,460 --> 00:08:34,559
See? You're crazy.
Grandpa says there's no ghost.

135
00:08:34,560 --> 00:08:37,880
Not crazy. If you don't believe me,
just watch tonight.

136
00:08:46,920 --> 00:08:49,720
- Wow...
- Wow...

137
00:08:50,060 --> 00:08:52,440
Hope it works.

138
00:09:00,520 --> 00:09:02,640
- So? How is it?
- Hmm.

139
00:09:12,450 --> 00:09:14,479
The new recipe hits the spot, huh?

140
00:09:14,480 --> 00:09:16,559
Uhm... thanks to our neighbor.

141
00:09:16,560 --> 00:09:18,080
- Mm...
- Hmm-mm.

142
00:09:20,380 --> 00:09:21,880
I've got this.

143
00:09:25,670 --> 00:09:26,760
Smells amazing.

144
00:09:32,150 --> 00:09:33,680
Where are you taking that?

145
00:09:33,830 --> 00:09:35,760
For Grandma to try.

146
00:09:36,040 --> 00:09:39,160
One bite and she'll be up dancing.
I'm sure.

147
00:09:40,260 --> 00:09:43,000
Wait. Put it down.
You're asking for trouble.

148
00:09:43,230 --> 00:09:44,320
Why?

149
00:09:44,460 --> 00:09:48,049
Because we didn't
preserve the recipe.

150
00:09:48,050 --> 00:09:50,480
That's disrespecting the elders.

151
00:09:50,510 --> 00:09:51,920
Yeah, fair point.

152
00:09:52,280 --> 00:09:54,479
We have to keep this under wraps.

153
00:09:54,480 --> 00:09:57,350
Grandma cannot find out about this.

154
00:09:57,570 --> 00:09:59,469
Hehe.

155
00:09:59,470 --> 00:10:00,519
Well, it tastes good.

156
00:10:00,520 --> 00:10:01,760
Cheers.

157
00:10:07,050 --> 00:10:09,560
Again, here's our plan.

158
00:10:09,580 --> 00:10:10,500
Mm-hmm.

159
00:10:10,520 --> 00:10:13,999
I'm meeting my friend here.
You hang back, take notes.

160
00:10:14,000 --> 00:10:15,000
Okay?

161
00:10:15,330 --> 00:10:18,000
Save, you really did
think this through?

162
00:10:18,100 --> 00:10:21,840
Aw, still on that? I'm fine.
Super easy.

163
00:10:24,040 --> 00:10:25,760
And did you bring cash?

164
00:10:26,120 --> 00:10:27,120
Got cash.

165
00:10:28,440 --> 00:10:30,080
But some shops don't take cash.

166
00:10:30,400 --> 00:10:33,000
Gotta pay through an app.
Do you know how?

167
00:10:33,350 --> 00:10:35,079
Come on. I know.

168
00:10:35,080 --> 00:10:37,600
I just put the phones
together, right?

169
00:10:37,890 --> 00:10:38,700
Mm-hmm.

170
00:10:38,720 --> 00:10:39,960
I've never done it though.

171
00:10:43,120 --> 00:10:44,400
Let me see your phone.

172
00:10:48,440 --> 00:10:49,440
Here.

173
00:10:52,240 --> 00:10:53,600
Okay. Let's see.

174
00:10:54,570 --> 00:10:58,330
Grandpa, you hardly have any apps.
None, even social media apps.

175
00:10:59,640 --> 00:11:02,920
I can make and receive calls.
Good enough for me.

176
00:11:03,190 --> 00:11:07,150
My friends still use landlines.

177
00:11:07,190 --> 00:11:08,710
- Hehe.
- Oh, impressive.

178
00:11:09,040 --> 00:11:10,760
Very, go on.

179
00:11:12,010 --> 00:11:13,560
Okay, just a sec.

180
00:11:16,760 --> 00:11:19,120
Come. Look at the camera.

181
00:11:19,610 --> 00:11:21,790
Look, look. There you go.

182
00:11:23,080 --> 00:11:25,640
Okay, blink. Blink.

183
00:11:26,680 --> 00:11:27,680
Blink again.

184
00:11:29,280 --> 00:11:32,320
Now smile. Show some teeth.

185
00:11:35,870 --> 00:11:37,960
Ah...

186
00:11:39,080 --> 00:11:39,880
Got it.
- That's it?
- Mm-hmm.

187
00:11:41,650 --> 00:11:42,650
Just a sec.

188
00:11:51,360 --> 00:11:53,040
Okay, done.

189
00:11:59,020 --> 00:12:00,020
Hmm?

190
00:12:02,170 --> 00:12:04,720
My friend just texted.
You just follow me.

191
00:12:42,460 --> 00:12:43,460
Hey, Guy.

192
00:12:46,500 --> 00:12:47,500
Here.

193
00:12:49,400 --> 00:12:50,400
What's that?

194
00:12:52,480 --> 00:12:53,560
Matching hats.

195
00:12:55,640 --> 00:12:56,720
Isn't that too much?

196
00:12:57,000 --> 00:12:58,680
So no one will make a move on you.

197
00:13:01,440 --> 00:13:03,560
I prefer this one
with my name on it.

198
00:13:12,500 --> 00:13:14,680
- You hungry yet?
- A little.

199
00:13:15,630 --> 00:13:16,880
Let's go then.

200
00:13:41,560 --> 00:13:42,560
Thank you.

201
00:13:48,760 --> 00:13:49,880
Hey, hold on.

202
00:13:54,530 --> 00:13:58,440
Stir-fried shrimp, extra chilies
with egg gravy on rice.

203
00:13:58,710 --> 00:14:00,320
I special-ordered your favorite.

204
00:14:01,560 --> 00:14:03,240
You know how I like this?

205
00:14:03,480 --> 00:14:04,480
I just know.

206
00:14:31,500 --> 00:14:33,020
Even napkins for each other.

207
00:14:34,520 --> 00:14:35,640
Is it good?

208
00:14:37,140 --> 00:14:38,200
Uh, mm-hmm.

209
00:14:39,840 --> 00:14:41,040
We'll come again.

210
00:14:51,390 --> 00:14:53,400
Hey, why's your face so red?

211
00:14:54,520 --> 00:14:55,560
You shy around me?

212
00:14:58,210 --> 00:14:59,210
The chili's hot.

213
00:15:08,720 --> 00:15:11,080
That shirt you had on earlier
was really something.

214
00:15:11,380 --> 00:15:14,660
- You're laying it on thick.
- I mean it. You looked great.

215
00:15:15,080 --> 00:15:17,160
- Shut up.
- Hehe.

216
00:15:21,120 --> 00:15:23,279
- Here, let me help.
- It's fine.

217
00:15:23,280 --> 00:15:25,320
- I'll get that.
- No, no. I've got this.

218
00:15:31,410 --> 00:15:32,410
Come on, let's walk.

219
00:16:18,640 --> 00:16:22,480
So this is what they call
a ship... ping moment.

220
00:16:38,530 --> 00:16:39,530
Wait.

221
00:16:40,370 --> 00:16:41,440
Where'd they go?

222
00:16:58,760 --> 00:17:02,120
Everything's so expensive
these days.

223
00:17:10,990 --> 00:17:12,670
Hi there, what can I get you?

224
00:17:12,980 --> 00:17:13,980
Oh.

225
00:17:15,120 --> 00:17:16,259
One of those, please.

226
00:17:16,260 --> 00:17:18,479
Sure. You can scan to pay
right here.

227
00:17:18,480 --> 00:17:19,720
Oh, scan.

228
00:17:23,390 --> 00:17:25,320
I'll need a screenshot
of the receipt.

229
00:17:29,120 --> 00:17:30,870
How do I do that?

230
00:17:31,010 --> 00:17:32,920
Uh, let me walk you through it.

231
00:17:33,310 --> 00:17:35,679
First, from your banking app,

232
00:17:35,680 --> 00:17:37,880
hit the scan button.

233
00:17:38,280 --> 00:17:39,280
Scan.

234
00:17:43,560 --> 00:17:44,560
Got it.

235
00:17:44,760 --> 00:17:46,040
Now tap confirm.

236
00:17:46,320 --> 00:17:47,320
Confirm.

237
00:17:48,200 --> 00:17:49,880
Payment's received.

238
00:18:15,080 --> 00:18:16,400
Turbo, hurry up.

239
00:18:18,960 --> 00:18:20,280
Nam Nile's already there.

240
00:18:20,330 --> 00:18:21,370
Okay, we move.

241
00:18:23,200 --> 00:18:25,040
Turbo.

242
00:18:25,880 --> 00:18:26,880
Nam Nile.

243
00:18:27,840 --> 00:18:28,840
Are those names?

244
00:18:33,260 --> 00:18:34,360
Turbo.

245
00:18:35,320 --> 00:18:36,740
Nam Nile.

246
00:18:37,010 --> 00:18:38,160
Weird names.

247
00:18:38,330 --> 00:18:39,560
So did you have fun?

248
00:18:40,930 --> 00:18:41,930
Uh-uh.

249
00:18:43,430 --> 00:18:44,950
You're just bad at the game.

250
00:18:44,980 --> 00:18:46,240
It was a hard game.

251
00:18:47,760 --> 00:18:51,200
Next time I'll coach you,
get you up to speed.

252
00:18:51,920 --> 00:18:52,960
Okay?

253
00:18:53,220 --> 00:18:55,719
Excuse me,
are you two free right now?

254
00:18:55,720 --> 00:18:57,840
We'd love to interview you.

255
00:18:58,200 --> 00:18:59,400
What about?

256
00:19:01,400 --> 00:19:03,120
Are you two a couple?

257
00:19:03,520 --> 00:19:05,400
We want to make
a couples content video.

258
00:19:07,920 --> 00:19:08,920
Not interested.

259
00:19:13,610 --> 00:19:14,880
Um, sorry about that.

260
00:19:16,000 --> 00:19:17,600
- Um.
- Hey, Save.

261
00:19:26,990 --> 00:19:27,990
Save.

262
00:19:31,120 --> 00:19:32,000
You okay?

263
00:19:32,001 --> 00:19:33,720
- Not on this side?
- No, no.

264
00:19:34,850 --> 00:19:35,850
Hmm?

265
00:19:35,930 --> 00:19:36,930
Hey.

266
00:19:37,500 --> 00:19:38,640
- There.
- I'm confused.

267
00:19:39,120 --> 00:19:40,600
- Turn right.
- Yeah, yeah.

268
00:19:40,930 --> 00:19:43,440
Okay, is that it?

269
00:20:23,300 --> 00:20:24,600
They said they wouldn't come.

270
00:20:25,520 --> 00:20:26,860
Guess they changed their minds.

271
00:20:29,840 --> 00:20:31,039
Hey, I'll be right back.

272
00:20:31,040 --> 00:20:32,040
Hey, Save.

273
00:20:58,680 --> 00:20:59,680
Hello.

274
00:20:59,840 --> 00:21:00,840
Where are you?

275
00:21:01,300 --> 00:21:05,930
It's like an open plaza.
A bunch of kids are playing.

276
00:21:06,390 --> 00:21:08,600
Okay, stay there.
I'm coming to you.

277
00:21:08,980 --> 00:21:09,980
Alright.

278
00:21:23,440 --> 00:21:25,600
Sir, can I get a quick interview?

279
00:21:28,490 --> 00:21:31,760
Sorry. I'm just waiting
for my grandson.

280
00:21:33,860 --> 00:21:37,080
Please, sir. I'll be quick.
I promise.

281
00:21:43,510 --> 00:21:45,710
Fine, just a sec then.

282
00:21:46,520 --> 00:21:47,520
Okay.

283
00:21:47,720 --> 00:21:49,359
I'll play you a dance clip.

284
00:21:49,360 --> 00:21:51,960
If you get the moves right,
that's 1,000 baht, yours to keep.

285
00:21:52,400 --> 00:21:54,760
Hmm? I can't dance.

286
00:21:55,000 --> 00:21:57,240
Alright then. How old are you?

287
00:21:58,440 --> 00:21:59,440
Seventy-five.

288
00:22:00,030 --> 00:22:02,590
Then 75 times that, all yours.

289
00:22:03,270 --> 00:22:08,200
Oh-ho. It's a lot of money.
You're giving it for free?

290
00:22:08,600 --> 00:22:10,490
I don't want it. Not dancing.

291
00:22:10,520 --> 00:22:11,750
It's not for free.

292
00:22:11,780 --> 00:22:12,440
Yeah?

293
00:22:12,490 --> 00:22:14,750
You just dance along
for everyone to watch.

294
00:22:14,990 --> 00:22:16,630
I told you, I can't dance.

295
00:22:16,830 --> 00:22:18,280
No need to be shy, sir.

296
00:22:18,770 --> 00:22:19,770
Hit it.

297
00:22:32,360 --> 00:22:33,580
Okay, that's enough.

298
00:22:33,870 --> 00:22:36,330
I'm going to find my grandson.

299
00:22:36,980 --> 00:22:39,760
Yo, guys, some noise for Grandpa.

300
00:22:39,790 --> 00:22:40,600
Dance.

301
00:22:40,620 --> 00:22:42,080
- Yo.
- Dance, dance.

302
00:22:43,480 --> 00:22:44,770
- Dance, Grandpa.
- Dance.

303
00:22:44,790 --> 00:22:47,360
You've gotta dance now. Watch me.

304
00:22:47,380 --> 00:22:49,380
- Dance, dance.
- Dance, dance.

305
00:22:49,630 --> 00:22:51,920
- Woo...
- Woo...

306
00:22:52,220 --> 00:22:53,600
Come on, sir. Just dance.

307
00:22:55,940 --> 00:22:57,680
Hey, stop, stop.

308
00:23:02,040 --> 00:23:03,120
Are you alright?

309
00:23:11,790 --> 00:23:13,760
It's for fun, lighten up.

310
00:23:14,230 --> 00:23:16,840
Fun how?
He didn't want to be filmed?

311
00:23:18,320 --> 00:23:21,360
Do not post it.
You know what PDPA is, right?

312
00:23:39,270 --> 00:23:40,270
Come sit here.

313
00:23:40,760 --> 00:23:42,040
- Hmm?
- This way.

314
00:23:51,500 --> 00:23:53,240
Are you okay?

315
00:23:54,380 --> 00:23:55,380
I'm fine.

316
00:23:56,450 --> 00:23:59,360
Next time, you can just walk away.

317
00:24:00,800 --> 00:24:03,480
Hmm. I just couldn't
find the opening.

318
00:24:04,800 --> 00:24:06,160
Don't worry about them.

319
00:24:06,600 --> 00:24:08,930
Mostly, all they want
is view counts.

320
00:24:09,490 --> 00:24:11,120
They don't care about privacy.

321
00:24:12,160 --> 00:24:14,400
I don't even know
why I had to dance.

322
00:24:18,320 --> 00:24:21,510
Okay... I'll walk slower.

323
00:24:22,950 --> 00:24:24,070
So you won't lose me again.

324
00:24:25,800 --> 00:24:26,800
Forget it.

325
00:24:29,040 --> 00:24:30,920
I really don't belong here.

326
00:24:32,280 --> 00:24:33,510
That's not true.

327
00:24:33,910 --> 00:24:37,980
Just because you don't play along
doesn't mean you don't fit in here.

328
00:24:39,240 --> 00:24:41,240
You just open up
to the right things.

329
00:24:41,960 --> 00:24:43,120
You'll be fine.

330
00:24:51,650 --> 00:24:52,680
So...

331
00:24:53,980 --> 00:24:55,120
let's just head home.

332
00:24:57,900 --> 00:24:59,880
Wait. I need to make a quick call.

333
00:25:10,920 --> 00:25:12,040
"Save."

334
00:25:14,650 --> 00:25:15,650
Where are you?

335
00:25:15,930 --> 00:25:16,930
I have to head back.

336
00:25:17,150 --> 00:25:18,160
Is everything okay?

337
00:25:18,720 --> 00:25:21,920
Yeah, I just remembered
I have to do something.

338
00:25:22,480 --> 00:25:23,520
See you at school.

339
00:25:25,180 --> 00:25:26,180
Save.

340
00:25:33,670 --> 00:25:34,670
Let's go.

341
00:25:42,250 --> 00:25:43,250
Easy, Grandpa.

342
00:25:50,280 --> 00:25:52,950
Excuse me, can I get
a quick interview for some content?

343
00:25:53,850 --> 00:25:56,440
Sorry. We can't.

344
00:26:01,080 --> 00:26:02,200
Oh, thank you.

345
00:26:05,990 --> 00:26:10,080
Just because you don't play along
doesn't mean you don't fit in here.

346
00:26:10,230 --> 00:26:12,300
You just open up
to the right things.

347
00:26:12,400 --> 00:26:13,400
You'll be fine.

348
00:26:13,720 --> 00:26:14,720
Hold on.

349
00:26:22,220 --> 00:26:23,760
What kind of content?

350
00:26:25,010 --> 00:26:26,120
- Oh...
- Hehe.

351
00:26:36,210 --> 00:26:41,400
Some new trends like kids' names.

352
00:26:41,690 --> 00:26:42,880
Turbo.

353
00:26:43,810 --> 00:26:46,400
Nam Nile.

354
00:26:47,800 --> 00:26:50,400
A guy in a skirt. Aw.

355
00:26:57,920 --> 00:27:01,280
"Turbo slung his navy backpack
over one shoulder,"

356
00:27:01,950 --> 00:27:06,750
"and made straight
for the meeting spot."

357
00:27:07,220 --> 00:27:09,960
"Dead center of Siam Square,"

358
00:27:10,640 --> 00:27:14,400
"a concrete jungle
stripped of every tree."

359
00:27:15,550 --> 00:27:20,080
"The air was thick with heat
baking off the pavement."

360
00:27:20,440 --> 00:27:24,690
"People moved fast,
like hunters on a trail."

361
00:27:25,920 --> 00:27:28,800
"And there stood Nam Nile,
waiting."

362
00:27:29,680 --> 00:27:33,160
"His scent drifted over,
soft and faint,"

363
00:27:33,740 --> 00:27:35,760
"like a bloom
luring something in."

364
00:27:37,200 --> 00:27:38,200
Come in.

365
00:27:42,800 --> 00:27:44,220
How are you doing?

366
00:27:44,240 --> 00:27:45,860
Got a lot written down?

367
00:27:46,170 --> 00:27:47,170
Yeah.

368
00:27:48,960 --> 00:27:50,680
I owe you a lot for this.

369
00:27:50,940 --> 00:27:51,940
Save.

370
00:27:53,120 --> 00:27:54,560
I want to ask you something.

371
00:27:55,170 --> 00:27:56,170
Yeah?

372
00:27:57,800 --> 00:28:00,880
When your guy held your hand...

373
00:28:01,560 --> 00:28:02,600
how did it feel?

374
00:28:10,720 --> 00:28:12,190
It was... strange, Grandpa.

375
00:28:12,210 --> 00:28:13,210
Hmm?

376
00:28:13,240 --> 00:28:14,879
Besides Dad and you,

377
00:28:14,880 --> 00:28:17,120
I've never been looked after
by another guy before.

378
00:28:17,860 --> 00:28:19,240
Did it feel good?

379
00:28:20,160 --> 00:28:21,160
Why do you ask?

380
00:28:21,240 --> 00:28:23,239
Well, I'm writing a novel.

381
00:28:23,240 --> 00:28:26,480
I need to understand
what the characters feel, deep down.

382
00:28:27,460 --> 00:28:29,920
So did you like it
when he held your hand?

383
00:28:30,720 --> 00:28:33,800
Why ask me? Use your imagination.

384
00:28:33,990 --> 00:28:34,990
Ah?

385
00:28:35,500 --> 00:28:39,040
You're here now
with firsthand experience.

386
00:28:39,230 --> 00:28:41,610
Why would I bother imagining?

387
00:28:41,640 --> 00:28:42,710
So?

388
00:28:43,970 --> 00:28:44,970
Um.

389
00:28:47,160 --> 00:28:48,160
Shy?

390
00:28:48,680 --> 00:28:50,520
Silly question? I'm going to bed.

391
00:28:50,540 --> 00:28:51,540
Hmm?

392
00:28:54,460 --> 00:28:55,460
Save.

393
00:28:57,110 --> 00:28:59,830
Hey, Save.

394
00:29:00,840 --> 00:29:02,080
What now?

395
00:29:02,640 --> 00:29:06,720
What you did today
was for my novel, wasn't it?

396
00:29:07,730 --> 00:29:08,730
Huh.

397
00:29:08,760 --> 00:29:09,840
Okay.

398
00:29:09,870 --> 00:29:11,050
What's the question again?

399
00:29:12,210 --> 00:29:14,480
When he held your hand,
did your heart race?

400
00:29:14,760 --> 00:29:15,680
Grandpa.

401
00:29:15,681 --> 00:29:17,000
Think about it.

402
00:29:36,380 --> 00:29:39,079
It didn't... race exactly.

403
00:29:39,080 --> 00:29:40,040
Oh?

404
00:29:40,041 --> 00:29:41,560
It was more like a jolt.

405
00:29:42,640 --> 00:29:43,790
Think about it.

406
00:29:44,040 --> 00:29:46,600
A guy who isn't my dad
grabbed my hand to cross the street.

407
00:29:47,520 --> 00:29:48,520
The feeling was...

408
00:29:51,590 --> 00:29:52,600
hard to put into words.

409
00:29:53,100 --> 00:29:54,140
Figure it out yourself.

410
00:29:55,400 --> 00:29:57,320
So that's what
the first step feels like.

411
00:29:59,670 --> 00:30:00,730
Satisfied now?

412
00:30:00,760 --> 00:30:02,680
Very. Thank you.

413
00:30:06,090 --> 00:30:07,090
Huh.

414
00:30:14,960 --> 00:30:16,280
Here we go.

415
00:30:17,340 --> 00:30:18,400
Okay, everyone line up.

416
00:30:18,810 --> 00:30:22,760
1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6, 7, 8,

417
00:30:23,360 --> 00:30:26,000
9, 10, 11, 12, 13.

418
00:30:28,790 --> 00:30:29,790
Who's missing?

419
00:30:30,000 --> 00:30:31,000
Who?

420
00:30:31,760 --> 00:30:32,760
Hmm?

421
00:30:33,470 --> 00:30:35,080
- Did he miscount?
- Who is it?

422
00:30:35,440 --> 00:30:36,520
- Dad.
- What?

423
00:30:36,550 --> 00:30:37,570
Someone's missing.

424
00:30:37,600 --> 00:30:38,480
What?
Who's gone?

425
00:30:39,390 --> 00:30:40,480
Phi Save.

426
00:30:41,680 --> 00:30:42,840
Jingjai's missing.

427
00:30:46,030 --> 00:30:46,830
Jingjai.

428
00:30:46,850 --> 00:30:54,160
- Jingjai, Jingjai.
- Jingjai.

429
00:30:54,650 --> 00:30:57,200
- Jingjai, where are you?
- Jingjai.

430
00:30:59,280 --> 00:31:02,000
There. The ghost child crying sound.

431
00:31:11,960 --> 00:31:13,040
Jingjai, where are you?

432
00:31:21,760 --> 00:31:22,760
Jingjai.

433
00:31:30,350 --> 00:31:32,710
Jingjai, why are you here?

434
00:31:37,660 --> 00:31:39,600
I don't want to go to school.

435
00:32:11,880 --> 00:32:14,240
Ghost? It's just Jingjai.

436
00:32:16,550 --> 00:32:18,080
How foolish of you, Jedi.

437
00:32:18,290 --> 00:32:21,040
Saw her from behind.
Thought it was a ghost.

438
00:32:29,980 --> 00:32:32,640
I miss Mom. I want to go home.

439
00:32:34,970 --> 00:32:39,040
Oh, Jingjai.
Your mom's not here anymore.

440
00:32:39,320 --> 00:32:41,360
She went to work in Lampang.

441
00:32:42,120 --> 00:32:44,000
I want to see Mom.

442
00:32:45,440 --> 00:32:47,840
When she's done working,
she'll come to visit.

443
00:32:48,120 --> 00:32:52,720
For now, you can do something
or play with your friends.

444
00:32:53,060 --> 00:32:54,060
How about that?

445
00:32:54,580 --> 00:32:57,840
Well, tell me about your friends.
How are they?

446
00:32:58,890 --> 00:32:59,890
Hmm?

447
00:33:01,920 --> 00:33:05,240
She doesn't really talk to anyone.
She mostly keeps to herself.

448
00:33:07,620 --> 00:33:10,600
Jingjai, you're going to
be here a while.

449
00:33:10,920 --> 00:33:13,680
You need to open up
and play with the other kids.

450
00:33:16,320 --> 00:33:18,940
And you still have to
go to school.

451
00:33:19,600 --> 00:33:22,080
When you get back,
I'll let you call Mom.

452
00:33:22,420 --> 00:33:24,200
Can I call her now?

453
00:33:24,440 --> 00:33:27,760
Afraid not. She's at work.

454
00:33:29,600 --> 00:33:32,400
I'll just wait till she's back.

455
00:33:42,010 --> 00:33:44,920
Jingjai, come to school with us.

456
00:33:46,120 --> 00:33:48,320
Yeah, school is fun.

457
00:33:48,740 --> 00:33:50,640
We'll do a lot of fun things.

458
00:33:54,000 --> 00:33:55,000
Like what?

459
00:34:06,360 --> 00:34:07,400
Go ahead.

460
00:34:11,320 --> 00:34:13,360
Alright, everyone's here.

461
00:34:13,640 --> 00:34:14,800
- Hmph.
- Hmm.

462
00:34:21,770 --> 00:34:22,800
Huh.

463
00:34:25,780 --> 00:34:26,930
Take a look at this.

464
00:34:26,960 --> 00:34:29,210
"Be Hard on Me, President."

465
00:34:50,810 --> 00:34:54,240
"Auntie Mart's Sanae Chan."

466
00:34:59,250 --> 00:35:03,600
Hello everyone,
presenting Sanae Chan desserts.

467
00:35:03,810 --> 00:35:07,039
Recipe passed down from grandma,
with a twist from the grandkids.

468
00:35:07,040 --> 00:35:12,000
One of a kind,
one with lots of love.

469
00:35:12,830 --> 00:35:16,440
So smash that cart.
Keep tapping, non-stop.

470
00:35:16,860 --> 00:35:20,759
Sixty baht a box. Buy three
and get free shipping nationwide.

471
00:35:20,760 --> 00:35:24,400
Wow...

472
00:35:24,810 --> 00:35:26,676
- "Lovely. Hard to find item."
- Oh, Phi Sorn, a comment.

473
00:35:26,700 --> 00:35:30,160
Thank you for that one viewer.

474
00:35:32,320 --> 00:35:37,880
This is a royal-style Sanae Chan
with a Japanese fusion twist.

475
00:35:38,160 --> 00:35:40,000
So delicious.

476
00:35:40,480 --> 00:35:42,120
Go ahead and add to cart.

477
00:35:42,140 --> 00:35:45,550
We'd love for you to try.
It's really that good.

478
00:35:53,360 --> 00:35:54,760
The viewer's gone.

479
00:35:54,790 --> 00:35:56,690
Hmm? Really?

480
00:35:58,070 --> 00:36:01,010
Mart, maybe I'll get to
the delivery app for now.

481
00:36:01,610 --> 00:36:03,000
Can you handle the live solo?

482
00:36:09,810 --> 00:36:12,970
Hey, why cut it off?
It's been only two hours.

483
00:36:13,100 --> 00:36:17,560
Right, two hours.
There's no sign of anybody now.

484
00:36:19,390 --> 00:36:22,200
How about I do a cartwheel
when selling it?

485
00:36:22,800 --> 00:36:28,200
Oh, no. You could hurt yourself,
old man.

486
00:36:28,660 --> 00:36:32,440
"Wow. This is way too sweet."

487
00:36:32,470 --> 00:36:34,620
"Someone give them
a proper BL series?"

488
00:36:34,780 --> 00:36:36,640
"BL done absolutely right."

489
00:36:40,320 --> 00:36:41,440
- Phi Sorn.
- Hmm?

490
00:36:41,620 --> 00:36:42,820
Is this our boy?

491
00:36:47,640 --> 00:36:48,720
- Save?
- Save?

492
00:36:51,780 --> 00:36:52,800
Hey.

493
00:36:53,520 --> 00:36:55,200
That's Save and Guy.

494
00:37:01,920 --> 00:37:04,440
Yo, why are you holding hands?

495
00:37:04,920 --> 00:37:09,000
Okay, are you two secretly
together or what?

496
00:37:10,960 --> 00:37:13,030
Ugh... we're not. Together how?

497
00:37:13,400 --> 00:37:16,320
People just ship us. Right, Guy?

498
00:37:18,200 --> 00:37:19,240
Tell them.

499
00:37:20,660 --> 00:37:23,720
Yeah, he was walking slow,
so I pulled him along.

500
00:37:24,120 --> 00:37:28,120
Yeah, right. Is that true?

501
00:37:29,160 --> 00:37:30,160
It is true.

502
00:37:30,220 --> 00:37:32,860
Hey, bunch of comments.
You're famous now.

503
00:37:33,860 --> 00:37:34,640
Let me see.

504
00:37:34,641 --> 00:37:36,200
Wow, so many.

505
00:37:36,640 --> 00:37:37,980
- Yeah, see?
- Yeah.

506
00:37:38,120 --> 00:37:39,260
Our friends have blown up.

507
00:37:41,520 --> 00:37:44,800
Hey, sorry I had to keep it
from everyone for now.

508
00:37:45,760 --> 00:37:46,880
You get it, right?

509
00:37:47,160 --> 00:37:48,240
Yeah, I get it.

510
00:37:50,750 --> 00:37:51,750
Thanks, man.

511
00:37:55,160 --> 00:37:56,160
Tell me something.

512
00:37:56,720 --> 00:37:58,640
That day we went out, were you okay?

513
00:37:59,280 --> 00:38:00,440
You left suddenly.

514
00:38:03,920 --> 00:38:05,400
Yeah, I was fine.

515
00:38:06,680 --> 00:38:08,800
I... really had something to do.

516
00:38:09,700 --> 00:38:10,800
Don't overthink it.

517
00:38:11,400 --> 00:38:14,120
How can I not?
You just disappeared on me.

518
00:38:15,520 --> 00:38:16,520
It was...

519
00:38:17,520 --> 00:38:18,840
my first time.

520
00:38:20,260 --> 00:38:21,860
I felt a little off.

521
00:38:23,480 --> 00:38:25,280
Just... give me some time.

522
00:38:26,640 --> 00:38:29,560
Sure. So that means
we'll have to go out more often.

523
00:38:29,960 --> 00:38:30,960
You'll get used to it.

524
00:38:32,950 --> 00:38:33,950
Mm-hmm.

525
00:39:17,760 --> 00:39:20,019
Hello, sweetheart, you're back.

526
00:39:20,020 --> 00:39:24,769
Now, now. Go wash up.
Then come down for dinner.

527
00:39:24,770 --> 00:39:26,679
All your favorites tonight.

528
00:39:26,680 --> 00:39:28,120
What's going on with you two?

529
00:39:28,750 --> 00:39:31,240
Acting like a pack of
pampering softies.

530
00:39:31,750 --> 00:39:34,360
Um, we'd just... like to talk to you.

531
00:39:34,600 --> 00:39:36,160
Eat first, then we'll talk.

532
00:39:36,180 --> 00:39:37,880
Whatever it is, just say it now.

533
00:39:44,000 --> 00:39:45,120
So, Mom, what's it about?

534
00:39:46,060 --> 00:39:48,240
Hey, I have no parts in this.

535
00:39:48,850 --> 00:39:51,080
They roped me here.

536
00:39:57,120 --> 00:39:59,039
We're family.

537
00:39:59,040 --> 00:40:01,440
We talk about anything, right?

538
00:40:02,100 --> 00:40:03,119
Right, Phi Sorn?

539
00:40:03,120 --> 00:40:04,120
Mm-hmm.

540
00:40:04,620 --> 00:40:07,640
You've always been a good kid.

541
00:40:07,670 --> 00:40:09,720
Whatever you are, whoever you like,

542
00:40:09,960 --> 00:40:12,430
Mom and Dad are fine with it.

543
00:40:13,080 --> 00:40:15,160
Just one thing.

544
00:40:15,420 --> 00:40:19,620
We want you to talk to us.
No secrets.

545
00:40:20,800 --> 00:40:23,920
Mom, just say it.
Stop going around the world.

546
00:40:24,660 --> 00:40:26,360
Are you dating a guy?

547
00:40:32,560 --> 00:40:35,120
- Snow, let us see it.
- Me too.

548
00:40:37,450 --> 00:40:39,000
When did you all get here?

549
00:40:39,800 --> 00:40:42,080
We saw Phi Save's clip.
He really is gay.

550
00:40:42,800 --> 00:40:44,599
Mom and Dad saw it too.

551
00:40:44,600 --> 00:40:47,400
Everyone calm down.
I don't like guys.

552
00:40:47,580 --> 00:40:48,740
You were holding hands.

553
00:40:48,940 --> 00:40:50,040
It's only the camera angle.

554
00:40:50,610 --> 00:40:54,040
Just come clean. We all support you.

555
00:40:54,070 --> 00:40:55,160
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

556
00:40:55,190 --> 00:40:56,519
I am genuinely not gay.

557
00:40:56,520 --> 00:40:59,079
Okay, let's all watch the clip.

558
00:40:59,080 --> 00:41:01,240
You believe it was
the camera angle?

559
00:41:04,500 --> 00:41:05,500
Hmm?

560
00:41:14,440 --> 00:41:16,840
Wait, the one behind you.

561
00:41:20,200 --> 00:41:21,360
Isn't that you, Father?

562
00:41:22,320 --> 00:41:23,920
That really is you.

563
00:41:26,660 --> 00:41:29,400
Dad... what were you doing?

564
00:41:32,680 --> 00:41:33,680
Oh, no.

565
00:41:34,270 --> 00:41:38,959
Snow, take everyone out.
It's serious. Out, out.

566
00:41:38,960 --> 00:41:40,840
- Please.
- I want to know.

567
00:41:40,870 --> 00:41:43,420
- This isn't for kids.
- I want to know.

568
00:41:43,450 --> 00:41:45,160
Out, out. That's an order.

569
00:41:45,180 --> 00:41:46,820
- No...
- I want to watch too.

570
00:41:46,850 --> 00:41:47,850
Huh.

571
00:41:51,760 --> 00:41:54,920
You said you were running errands.
What exactly was it?

572
00:41:57,040 --> 00:41:58,080
Ahem.

573
00:41:58,190 --> 00:41:59,190
Well...

574
00:42:01,230 --> 00:42:02,840
I tried dating a friend...

575
00:42:04,050 --> 00:42:06,730
- to help Grandpa with the novel.
- What?

576
00:42:07,440 --> 00:42:09,920
You date a friend to help him write?

577
00:42:09,940 --> 00:42:12,260
And you were okay with this?

578
00:42:12,280 --> 00:42:13,450
I wasn't okay.

579
00:42:13,650 --> 00:42:14,480
Hmm?

580
00:42:14,510 --> 00:42:16,000
But it really helped me write.

581
00:42:16,030 --> 00:42:17,480
Good grief.

582
00:42:17,840 --> 00:42:21,320
Okay. Don't worry.
I genuinely don't like guys.

583
00:42:22,080 --> 00:42:23,280
I just wanted to help Grandpa.

584
00:42:24,690 --> 00:42:25,970
This has gone off the rails.

585
00:42:26,810 --> 00:42:30,690
Wait. Doesn't that mean
you misled your friend?

586
00:42:31,610 --> 00:42:32,920
Well, I didn't.

587
00:42:33,540 --> 00:42:36,680
Just... exploring. Learning.

588
00:42:38,280 --> 00:42:41,480
And what if it turns out
to be real? What then?

589
00:42:44,900 --> 00:42:45,900
Well...

590
00:42:45,950 --> 00:42:49,120
until that day comes,
don't get ahead of yourself.

591
00:42:50,510 --> 00:42:53,560
Is this... a good idea?

592
00:42:54,000 --> 00:42:55,920
And is your friend okay with this?

593
00:42:56,800 --> 00:42:57,840
He's fine.

594
00:42:59,050 --> 00:43:00,559
I invited him here tomorrow.

595
00:43:00,560 --> 00:43:01,560
What?

596
00:43:01,670 --> 00:43:02,670
What for?

597
00:43:05,360 --> 00:43:06,800
I asked him to do that.

598
00:43:08,510 --> 00:43:09,760
Need more material.

599
00:43:09,890 --> 00:43:12,440
- Oh, my head.
- Oh boy.

600
00:43:27,300 --> 00:43:29,250
- Ooh, pinching cheeks.
- Pinch.

601
00:43:29,270 --> 00:43:30,270
Jingjai.

602
00:43:31,220 --> 00:43:31,960
Yes?
How are you doing?

603
00:43:33,800 --> 00:43:37,120
I'm okay. I'll be good
and wait for Mom and Dad.

604
00:43:37,140 --> 00:43:39,640
Oh... that's great.

605
00:43:39,960 --> 00:43:43,040
Every new kid here
goes through the same thing.

606
00:43:43,290 --> 00:43:45,920
But you'll find your footing.

607
00:43:46,320 --> 00:43:48,960
Snow, look after Jingjai.

608
00:43:49,240 --> 00:43:50,960
Yes, Grandpa. Understood.

609
00:43:52,650 --> 00:43:54,160
Make friends. Don't tease her.

610
00:43:55,080 --> 00:43:56,560
Absolutely, Director.

611
00:43:59,240 --> 00:44:00,280
What are you all watching?

612
00:44:00,960 --> 00:44:02,320
A BL drama.

613
00:44:02,350 --> 00:44:03,350
Just a sec.

614
00:44:17,590 --> 00:44:18,679
Are you nervous?

615
00:44:18,680 --> 00:44:21,760
Not at all.
I'm not about to propose.

616
00:44:24,210 --> 00:44:25,280
Come on. Let's go.

617
00:44:30,540 --> 00:44:31,840
Hello.

618
00:44:32,080 --> 00:44:33,160
Hello.

619
00:44:33,190 --> 00:44:34,390
Oh, hello, hello.

620
00:44:37,550 --> 00:44:38,920
You must be Guy.

621
00:44:39,090 --> 00:44:40,090
Yes, I am.

622
00:44:42,160 --> 00:44:45,200
Phi Guy, I'm Snow,
Phi Save's little sister.

623
